hopobject.body: Could you tell me the dialing code for ? generic pharmacy tagline Severed from the sun-baked mainland by the Straits of Messina, and on roughly the same latitude as Tunisia's north coast, Sicily has an identity, culture and even language distinctly different from the rest of Italy. It lies at a crossroads where historic trade routes met, and has ruins and riches from the Phoenician, Roman, Byzantine, Greek and Arab periods: from Palermo, the northern capital, with its 12th-century church of La Martorana, to the Greek temples at Agrigento (on the south coast), Syracuse and Taormina (the east coast) and the Roman mosaics of Piazza Armerina (in the centre).
